[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{You have a terrible hand but you still cannot pass partner's double. He is requesting you to bid 2\C as a relay bid so he can name his suit.

You dutifully respond 2\C and he says 2\H.  

You didn't want to bid the first time, this time you definitely pass.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:A763.63.AKJ.QJT2 KJ9.A4.Q872.A965 2.KJ75.T964.K843 QT854.QT982.53.7"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "2S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1NT pass pass 2H pass 2S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "e0e55049aa97a93d9a45e91e715b7019380dc62d440d7fbf07bea6b25bfa553a"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{OK, you only have 4 HCP. But you have 10 cards in the Majors. And, you are in the balancing seat. If West is willing to let it die at 1NT your partner must have some strength. So you should use DONT. Youbid 2\H, showing both Major suits.

Partner responds 2\S.  

Partner prefers \Ss to \Hs. Since you were bare minimum you pass.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "N"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "N:KQT6.AQT.JT3.K84 83.KJ82.964.AQ73 J42.9754.A8.JT92 A975.63.KQ752.65"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "2D"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "N"]
1NT pass pass 2D pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 0, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "9c27797ab2d4f7faeccb9436d9700ff44449dad304e418df47665fbf2b05445f"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{Your hand is too balanced to intervene over North's 1NT so you pass.

Then partner overcalls 2\D.  

Partner has two suits, \Ds and one of the Majors. If his other suit is \Hs then a 2\H bid by you would work great. But if his other suit is \Ss anything you say would not be good.

Since you can tolerate \Ds your safest call is pass.}

